cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with learning a hierarchical shape vocabulary for object representation. The use of machine learning techniques for learning the vocabulary also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for object recognition. The use of recursive combinations and fast inference also suggests that it could belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the experimental results involve the use of images, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
